Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20need%20to%20earn%20%24952%2C902%20a%20year%20to%20be%20in%20the%20top%201%25%20in%20Connecticut.%20In%20West%20Virginia%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20you%20need%20just%20%24374%2C712.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20according%20to%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fdata-studies%2Ftop-1-percent-income-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20SmartAsset%2C%20which%20calculated%20the%20income%20required%20to%20reach%20the%20highest-earning%201%25%20in%20each%20of%20the%20USA's%2050%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20analyzed%202020%20data%20from%20the%20IRS%20for%20individual%20tax%20filers%20and%20adjusted%20the%20figures%20to%20May%202023%20dollars%20using%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics'%20Consumer%20Price%20Index.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%20across%20the%20US%2C%20you%20need%20%24652%2C657%20to%20be%20classed%20as%20part%20of%20the%20top%201%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnecticut%20topped%20the%20list%2C%20with%20households%20needing%20an%20annual%20income%20of%20close%20to%20%241%20million%20to%20make%20the%20top%201%25.%20The%20state%20median%20income%20for%20a%20one-person%20household%20is%20%2466%2C270%2C%20rising%20to%20%2486%2C661%20for%20two%20people%2C%20%24107%2C052%20for%20three%2C%20and%20%24127%2C443%20for%20four%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acf.hhs.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Focs%2FCOMM_LIHEAP_Att1SMITable_FY2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Social%20Services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnecticut%20is%20followed%20by%20Massachusetts%2C%20California%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Washington%20D.C.%20were%20a%20state%2C%20it%20would%20have%20come%20first%20in%20SmartAsset's%20ranking%2C%20with%20an%20annual%20income%20of%20%241%2C013%2C698%20required%20to%20be%20in%20the%20capital's%20top%201%25.%3