ill%20now%20be%20rewarded%20equally%2C%E2%80%9D%20ICC%20chairman%20Greg%20Barclay%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%202017%20we%20have%20increased%20prize%20money%20at%20women%E2%80%99s%20events%20every%20year%20with%20a%20clear%20focus%20on%20reaching%20equal%20prize%20money%20and%20from%20here%20on%20in%2C%20winning%20the%20ICC%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%20will%20carry%20the%20same%20prize%20money%20as%20winning%20the%20ICC%20Men%E2%80%99s%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%20and%20the%20same%20for%20T20%20World%20Cups%20and%20U19s%20too.%20Cricket%20is%20genuinely%20a%20sport%20for%20all%20and%20this%20decision%20from%20the%20ICC%20Board%20reinforces%20that%20and%20enables%20us%20to%20celebrate%20and%20value%20every%20single%20player%E2%80%99s%20contribution%20to%20the%20game%20equally%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20winners%20and%20runners-up%20at%20the%20ICC%20Women%E2%80%99s%20T20%20World%20Cup%202020%20and%202023%20received%20%241%20million%20and%20%24500%2C000%20respectively%2C%20which%20was%20five%20times%20the%20amount%20offered%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689325257000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F14134600%2Findian-womens-cricket-team-picture-2022.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Finternational-cricket-council-says-prizes-for-mens-and-womens-teams-will-now-be-equal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20decision%20was%20made%20during%20the%20ICC%20Annual%20Conference%20held%20in%20Durban%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20and%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Council's%20plan%20to%20achieve%20pay%20parity%20by%202030.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Finternational-cricket-council-says-prizes-for-mens-and-womens-teams-will-now-be-equal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20went%20to%20Phillips%20Exeter%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20elite%20boarding%20schools%20in%20America.%20It%20changed%20my%20life%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn't%20send%20my%20kids%20there.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221274%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kelly%20Johnson-Arbor%20sitting%20in%20a%20pink%20jacket%20in%20front%20of%20a%20blue%20wall%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b01ad2c22d1a00194548cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22956%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKelly%20Johnson-Arbor.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kelly%20Johnson-Arbor%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKelly%20Johnson-Arbor%20said%20Phillips%20Exeter%20stabilized%20her%20life%20and%20helped%20her%20overcome%20shyness.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETuition%20with%20boarding%20costs%20more%20than%20%2460%2C000%20a%20year%20for%20students%20without%20financial%20aid%20now.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20she%20had%20a%20positive%20experience%2C%20she%20decided%20not%20to%20send%20her%20own%20children%20to%20boarding%20school.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Kelly%20Johnson-Arbor%2C%20a%20physician%20based%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20physician%2C%20board%20certified%20in%20emergency%20medicine%2C%20medical%20toxicology%2C%20and%20undersea%20and%20hyperbaric%20medicine.%20I'm%20the%20medical%20director%20and%20interim%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Capital%20Poison%20Center%2C%20and%20I%20practice%20hyperbaric%20medicine%20and%20toxicology%20at%20MedStar%20Georgetown%20University%20Hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.exeter.edu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPhillips%20Exeter%20Academy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niche.com%2Fk12%2Fsearch%2Fbest-boarding-high-schools%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eis%20ranked%20by%20Niche%20as%20the%20third-best%20boarding%20high%20school%20in%20America%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20started%20at%20the%20school%20in%201989%2C%20when%20I%20was%2015%2C%20and%20graduated%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20overcame%20many%20challenges%20but%20had%20a%20positive%20experience%20overall.%20The%20school%20gave%20me%20extra%20confidence%20and%20a%20great%20education%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20boarding%20school%20is%20the%20right%20fit%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMany%20people%20think%20that%20all%20kids%20who%20go%20to%20elite%20boarding%20schools%20are%20wealthy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20true%20for%20some%2C%20but%20I%20was%20completely%20the%20opposite.%20I%20grew%20up%20the%20only%20child%20of%20a%20single%20mother%20in%20Anchorage%2C%20Alaska.%20I%20didn't%20meet%20my%20father%20until%20I%20was%20in%20my%2020s.%20My%20upbringing%20was%20very%20sheltered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20was%20a%20teacher%2C%20but%20earlier%20in%20her%20career%2C%20she%20had%20been%20a%20television%20journalist%20and%20worked%20in%20a%20nightclub.%20She%20had%20friends%20who%20sent%20their%20kids%20to%20boarding%20schools%2C%20and%20she%20wanted%20me%20to%20have%20that%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20never%20could've%20afforded%20the%20fees%2C%20so%20I%20went%20there%20on%20a%20scholarship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20recall%20the%20fees%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20they're%20now%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.exeter.edu%2Fadmissions-and-financial-aid%2Ftuition-financial-aid%2Fpayment-options%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eover%20%2460%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20boarding%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20a%20scholarship%2C%20I%20had%20to%20take%20the%20Preliminary%20SAT%2C%20which%20a%20lot%20of%20boarding%20schools%20use%20to%20measure%20applicants.%20I%20started%20interviewing%20with%20major%20East%20Coast%20schools%20when%20I%20was%20in%20eighth%20grade.%20My%20mom%20rented%20the%20cheapest%20car%20possible%20to%20drive%20us%20to%20the%20interviews%2C%20and%20we%20used%20food%20stamps%20for%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20schools%20interviewed%20the%20parents%20and%20the%20students%2C%20and%20I%20deferred%20mostly%20to%20my%20mother.%20I%20remember%20the%20interviewer%20at%20Andover%2C%20another%20school%20I%20applied%20to%2C%20asked%20my%20mom%20why%20I%20didn't%20do%20more%20chores%20at%20home.%20She%20took%20that%20to%20mean%20that%20the%20interviewer%20didn't%20think%20I%20was%20mature%20enough%20for%20the%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20accepted%20to%20Phillips%20Exeter%20and%20moved%20to%20Exeter%2C%20New%20Hampshire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20quite%20a%20shock%20because%20I%20had%20to%20leave%20my%20home%20in%20Alaska%2C%20move%20across%20the%20country%2C%20and%20live%20in%20a%20dormitory%20with%20people%20I'd%20never%20met%20before%20who%20came%20from%20completely%20different%20backgrounds%20than%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20looked%20very%20different%20than%20me.%20My%20mom%20was%20Black%2C%20and%20my%20father%20is%20white%2C%20so%20I%20was%20a%20minority%20at%20Exeter.%20That%20was%20pretty%20rare%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20a%20boarding%20student%20for%203%20years%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20initial%20culture%20shock%2C%20I%20came%20to%20really%20like%20it.%20I%20know%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20enjoy%20the%20boarding-school%20experience%2C%20but%20I%20always%20wanted%20to%20get%20away%20from%20home%20and%20be%20independent.%20I'm%20still%20a%20pretty%20independent%20person%2C%20and%20I%20think%20much%20of%20that%20comes%20from%20Exeter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20away%20from%20home%20was%20the%20best%20thing%20for%20me%20%E2%80%94%20my%20mother%20faced%20homelessness%20around%20that%20time%20and%20was%20living%20in%20transient%20hotels.%20Campus%20for%20me%20was%20a%20stable%20place%20with%20three%20meals%20a%20day%2C%20a%20room%20to%20go%20to%2C%20and%20clean%20laundry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20made%20some%20really%20good%20friends%20there%2C%20and%20I%20still%20keep%20in%20touch%20with%20many%20of%20them.%20The%20bonds%20that%20we%20made%20at%20Exeter%20were%20very%20strong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBefore%20Exeter%2C%20I%20was%20painfully%20shy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoarding%20school%20definitely%20helped%20me%20get%20past%20my%20shyness%20and%20set%20me%20up%20for%20my%20career.%20Classes%20at%20Exeter%20are%20held%20around%20an%20oval-shaped%20table%20called%20the%20Harkness%20table%20that's%20supposed%20to%20promote%20open%20discussion%20and%20democratic%20learning.%20You%20have%20to%20speak%20to%20get%20a%20good%20grade%2C%20and%20there's%20nowhere%20to%20hide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20that%2C%20I%20never%20spoke%20to%20people%20spontaneously.%20I'm%20completely%20different%20now.%20I%20learned%20not%20to%20be%20afraid%20when%20I%20want%20to%20speak%20up.%20As%20a%2015-year-old%2C%20it%20was%20a%20very%20important%20lesson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20take%20classes%20in%20Greek%20and%20Latin%20and%20other%20subjects%20that%20weren't%20offered%20in%20high%20schools%20in%20Alaska.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EExeter%20was%20socially%20challenging%20at%20times%2C%20especially%20as%20a%20scholarship%20student%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20having%20the%20financial%20resources%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20other%20students%20had%20was%20the%20biggest%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20knew%20who%20was%20on%20scholarship%20because%20we%20had%20to%20do%20jobs%20around%20campus%20to%20help%20pay%20our%20way.%20My%20job%20was%20delivering%20the%20daily%20bulletin%2C%20so%20my%20circumstances%20were%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20scholarship%20kids%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20make%20these%20disparities%20less%20visible.%20We%20ate%20in%20a%20dining%20hall%2C%20and%20if%20the%20rich%20kids%20didn't%20like%20the%20food%2C%20they%20could%20just%20go%20and%20buy%20pizza.%20We%20couldn't%20afford%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20one%20of%20my%20friends%20found%20a%20pizza%20place%20in%20town%20that%20sold%20breadsticks%20for%20a%20dollar%20and%20put%20them%20in%20pizza%20boxes.%20After%20that%2C%20we%20could%20walk%20around%20campus%20with%20pizza%20boxes%2C%20too%2C%20and%20we%20would%20blend%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20dress%20code%20also%20taught%20me%20a%20lot%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20standards%20to%20enforce%20discipline.%20I%20got%20sent%20home%20from%20class%20once%20because%20I%20was%20wearing%20cutoff%20shorts%20that%20I%20had%20rolled%20up.%20That%20wasn't%20allowed%20%E2%80%94%20shorts%20had%20to%20have%20a%20hem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20now%20comfortable%20dressing%20up%20in%20my%20daily%20life.%20For%20most%20people%2C%20this%20isn't%20a%20big%20deal%2C%20but%20when%20you're%20poor%20and%20come%20from%20an%20environment%20where%20you%20don't%20wear%20nice%20clothes%20on%20a%20regular%20basis%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20get%20that%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EExeter%20prepared%20me%20for%20Harvard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20boarding%20school%2C%20I%20learned%20about%20the%20opposite%20sex%2C%20drinking%2C%20and%20socioeconomic%20disparities%20at%20a%20much%20younger%20age%20than%20most%20other%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20graduated%20and%20went%20to%20Harvard%20for%20college%2C%20it%20was%20all%20out%20of%20my%20system.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20other%20freshmen%20in%20college%20were%20going%20out%20and%20partying%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20already%20been%20in%20a%20dorm%20for%20three%20years%2C%20and%20unlike%20most%20of%20my%20peers%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20those%20temptations%20that%20came%20from%20being%20away%20from%20home%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20glad%20I%20went%20to%20Exeter%20%E2%80%94%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20where%20I%20am%20today%20without%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20for%20everyone%2C%20though.%20My%20children%20are%2010%20and%2012%2C%20and%20given%20their%20more%20comfortable%20upbringing%2C%20I%20couldn't%20picture%20sending%20them%20away%20to%20boarding%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20environment%20that%20favors%20people%20who%20are%20very%20mentally%20strong%2C%20and%20by%20their%20age%2C%20I'd%20faced%20so%20much%20more%20than%20they%20have.%20I've%20tried%20to%20protect%20them%20and%20nurture%20them%20so%20they%20don't%20need%20a%20school%20like%20Exeter%20to%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphillips-exeter-academy-changed-life-wouldnt-send-kids-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689325201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b01afa9751e3001929f68a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphillips-exeter-academy-changed-life-wouldnt-send-kids-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20physician%20Kelly%20Johnson-Arbor%20enrolled%20in%20Phillips%20Exeter%20Academy%20in%201989.%20The%20elite%20boarding%20school%20helped%20her%20develop%20her%20confidence%20and%20led%20her%20to%20Harvard.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Elle%20Hardy)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphillips-exeter-academy-changed-life-wouldnt-send-kids-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20renovated%20a%20100-year-old%20home%20into%20a%2070s-themed%20Airbnb%20that%20brings%20in%20thousands%20a%20month.%20Here's%20how%20we%20did%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%