er%20is%20an%20e-commerce%20entrepreneur%20who%20made%20over%20%24945%2C000%20in%20her%20first%20year%20on%20Etsy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShe%20says%20the%20easiest%20Etsy%20niches%20are%20print-on-demand%20products%20and%20small-parcel%20accessories.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHer%20biggest%20advice%20is%20to%20set%20proper%20expectations%20for%20the%20niche%20that%20you're%20entering.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20graduated%20college%20in%202018%2C%20I%20never%20had%20a%20regular%20job.%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20an%20entrepreneur.%20Back%20then%2C%20the%20biggest%20thing%20was%20media%20buying%2C%20like%20doing%20Facebook%20ads%2C%20Instagram%20ads%2C%20and%20Google%20ads%20for%20people.%20So%20I%20started%20teaching%20myself%20by%20learning%20from%20YouTube%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20broke%2C%20you%20say%20yes%20to%20everybody.%20I%20tried%20to%20build%20a%20media-buying%20agency%20specifically%20for%20doctors.%20I%20went%20to%20every%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%20meeting%20from%20Miami%20to%20West%20Palm.%20When%20it%20was%20my%20time%20to%20pitch%20my%20services%2C%20I%20was%20just%20horrible%20at%20it.%20I%20did%20that%20for%20two%20months%20and%20ended%20up%20getting%20zero%20clients%20in%20the%20medical%20field.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20time%20went%20on%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20undercharging%20for%20my%20services%20while%20overdelivering%20to%20my%20clients%2C%20which%20eventually%20led%20to%20burnout.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20clients%20back%20then%20had%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-6-figures-etsy-print-on-demand-sellers-2023-4%5C%22%3EEtsy%20shop%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20she%20was%20selling%20products%20both%20on%20an%20Etsy%20shop%20and%20a%20Shopify%20Store.%20While%20managing%20her%20ads%2C%20I%20discovered%20that%20working%20with%20Etsy%20was%20so%20much%20easier%20than%20media%20buying.%20That's%20how%20I%20got%20into%20the%20Etsy%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20wasn't%20the%20standard%20DIY%20or%20handmade%20crafts%20Etsy%20shop%20owner%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20make%20crafts%20or%20other%20handmade%20products%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20the%20give-me-something-to-sell-and-I-will-sell-it%20type%20of%20Etsy%20shop%20owner.%20I%20found%20a%20production%20partner%20online%20by%20just%20a%20regular%20Google%20Search%20and%20also%20hired%20a%20designer.%20I%20tested%20out%20a%20few%20partners%20before%20settling%20on%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETogether%2C%20we%20focused%20on%20the%20fast%20fashion%20accessory%20niche.%20Our%20manufacturer%20was%20in%20Brazil%20and%20we%20became%20very%20close.%20If%20we%20had%20new%20designs%2C%20we%20could%20have%20the%20inventory%20ready%20within%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2020%20was%20just%20this%20magical%20year%20when%20the%20business%20started%20really%20pumping.%20In%20December%202019%2C%20our%20total%20revenue%20got%20up%20to%20%2430%2C000.%20One%20of%20our%20highest%20months%20was%20actually%20August%202020%20%E2%80%94%20we%20did%20almost%20%24200%2C000%20in%20total%20revenue%20with%20Etsy%20and%20Shopify%20combined.%20It%20was%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20handled%20every%20aspect%20of%20the%20business%20on%20my%20own.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20I%20reached%20my%20second%20%24200%2C000%20month%20that%20I%20finally%20decided%20to%20hire%20my%20first%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrint-on-demand%20is%20the%20easiest%20for%20new%20beginners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprint-on-demand-business-etsy-profitable-listings-tips-2023-5%5C%22%3EPrint-on-demand%3C%2Fa%3E%20service%20is%20the%20easiest%20niche%20for%20new%20Etsy%20sellers%2C%20then%20small%20parcel%20accessories%20because%20the%20barrier%20of%20entry%20is%20so%20low.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Etsy%20world%2C%20sellers%20are%20more%20reserved%20with%20their%20funds.%20So%20the%20print-on-demand%20realm%20is%20very%20appealing%20to%20people%20because%20you%20don't%20pay%20for%20the%20product%20until%20it%20sells.%20It%20mitigates%20the%20risk%20and%20you%20can%20scale%20very%2C%20very%20fast.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20best%20for%20scaling%2C%20I%20would%20say%2C%20is%20the%20small%20parcel%20accessory%20world.%20Small%20parcels%20are%20items%20that%20can%20be%20shipped%20via%20USPS%20First%20Class%20Mail%2C%20which%20entails%204-7%20day%20shipping.%20This%20option%20is%20the%20cheapest%20for%20items%20weighing%20less%20than%20one%20pound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEssential%20tips%20to%20start%20your%20first-ever%20Print-on-demand%20Etsy%20store%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Define%20your%20brand%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20starting%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20you%20want%20to%20define%20your%20brand%20to%20make%20it%20recognizable.%20It's%20like%20when%20you%20walk%20into%20Hollister%20versus%20American%20Eagle%2C%20they're%20similar%2C%20but%20still%20different.%20You%20want%20to%20maintain%20that%20level%20of%20consistency%20to%20be%20able%20to%20build%20a%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20people%20are%20kind%20of%20doing%20now%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20is%20they're%20just%20coming%20in%20and%20launching%20random%20products%20%E2%80%94%20nothing's%20in%20sync.%20We%20don't%20want%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20we%20want%20to%20create%20a%20brand%20identity%20that%20can%20easily%20translate%20into%20Shopify%20later%20on.%20Take%20into%20account%20factors%20like%20color%20schemes%2C%20brand%20identity%2C%20and%20other%20elements%20that%20contribute%20to%20a%20cohesive%20brand%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E2.%20%3Cstrong%3EIntegrate%20your%20Etsy%20shop%20with%20tools%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20thing%20is%20integrating%20tools%20with%20your%20shops%2C%20such%20as%20Printify%2C%20Mydesigns%2C%20or%20Printful%2C%20the%20middleman%20that%20connects%20you%20to%20those%20print%20providers.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20you%20get%20an%20order%20from%20your%20Etsy%20shop%2C%20Printfuls%20will%20print%20it%20and%20fulfill%20it%20for%20you.%20I%20really%20like%20MyDesigns%20specifically%20because%20they%20can%20bulk%20upload%20a%20bunch%20of%20listings%20at%20once.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20use%20tools%20like%20Canva%20for%20design.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20making%20your%20designs%2C%20you%20should%20do%20research%20on%20the%20market%20to%20see%20what's%20selling.%20We%20usually%20type%20in%20keywords%20in%20the%20search%20bar%20and%20try%20to%20find%20other%20listings%20that%20have%20%26quot%3Bbest%20seller%26quot%3B%20badges.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20there%20are%204%2C000%20monthly%20searches%20for%20%26quot%3BBaby%20Bows%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20a%20considerable%20search%20volume%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20include%20%26quot%3BBaby%20Bows%26quot%3B%20in%20your%20title%20and%20create%20a%20competitive%20listing%20in%20comparison%20to%20the%20top%20performers%20for%20that%20keyword.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20then%20look%20at%20those%20designs%20and%20try%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20we%20can%20improve%20upon%20them%2C%20or%20how%20we%20can%20add%20value%20to%20our%20listings.%20These%20people%20are%20at%20the%20top%20of%20these%20micro%20niches%2C%20but%20we're%20careful%20not%20to%20blatantly%20copy%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Do%20a%20competitor%20analysis%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EEtsy%20launched%20its%20own%20competitor%20analysis%20tools%2C%20too.%20One%20tip%20is%20to%20look%20at%20the%20key%20attributes%20of%20why%20those%20listings%20are%20the%20top%20for%20that%20keyword.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20need%20to%20analyze%20the%20trends%20they%20are%20following%2C%20the%20fonts%20they%20are%20using%2C%20whether%20they%20say%20something%20fun%20in%20their%20listings%2C%20the%20options%20they%20offer%2C%20their%20price%20point%2C%20whether%20they%20are%20running%20daily%20sales%2C%20the%20number%20of%20photos%20they%20feature%2C%20and%20the%20appearance%20of%20their%20mockups.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20common%20mistakes%20Print-on-Demand%20sellers%20should%20avoid%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20mistakes%20POD%20people%20can%20make%20is%20rushing%20through%20the%20launching%20process%2C%20especially%20if%20they're%20new%20to%20design.%20They%20might%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BLet%20me%20just%20launch.%26quot%3B%20But%20their%20products%20are%20lacking%20in%20quality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20POD%20sellers%20fail%20to%20establish%20a%20functional%20business%20model.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20come%20to%20Etsy%20don't%20want%20to%20invest%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20just%20not%20the%20biggest%20risk-takers.%20When%20it%20comes%20time%20to%20scale%2C%20they're%20so%20unprepared%20and%20they%20haven't%20set%20up%20their%20business%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20useful%20approach%20in%20this%20regard%20is%20to%20write%20out%20every%20if-then%20scenario.%20After%20answering%20a%20ton%20of%20customer%20service%20questions%20with%20buyers%2C%20you%20should%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20about%20your%20customers%20and%20be%20able%20to%20list%20the%20top%2050%20most%20commonly%20asked%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20you%20should%20know%20about%20your%20fulfillment%20process%2C%20the%20quality%20control%20process%20for%20print-on-demand%2C%20the%20design%20process%2C%20research%20for%20print-on-demand%2C%20the%20research%2C%20and%20development%20process%2C%20as%20well%20as%20how%20you%20determine%20your%20priorities%20and%20what%20to%20design%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemember%3A%20this%20is%20a%20marathon%2C%20not%20a%20sprint%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20advice%20I%20would%20give%20to%20someone%20who%20wants%20to%20start%20an%20Etsy%20business%20is%20to%20set%20proper%20expectations%20for%20the%20niche%20that%20you're%20entering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Etsy%20online%20game%20is%20all%20about%20long-term%20business%20building.%20It's%20not%20a%20%26quot%3BGet%20Rich%20Quick%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BHow%20I%20can%20get%20to%201000%20listings%20in%2030%20days%26quot%3B%20kind%20of%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20focus%20is%20on%20building%20scalable%20systems%20so%20your%20business%20is%20constantly%20growing.%20The%20simplest%20example%20is%20with%20your%20listings%2C%20your%20launch%20strategy%20should%20be%20repeatable%20and%20consistent%20from%20week%20to%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you're%20an%20Etsy%20shop%20owner%20and%20would%20like%20to%20share%20your%20story%2C%20email%20Aria%20yang%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aayang%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eayang%40insider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fetsy-shop-owner-million-revenue-best-tips-for-success-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689325200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b075ac9751e300192a0d1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fetsy-shop-owner-million-revenue-best-tips-for-success-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hannah%20Gardner%20made%20over%20%24945%2C000%20in%20her%20first%20year%20on%20Etsy.%20She%20shares%20her%20essential%20tips%20when%20starting%20an%20Etsy%20shop%20and%20mistakes%20to%20avoid.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Aria%20Yang)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fetsy-shop-owner-million-revenue-best-tips-for-success-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ITV%20%E2%80%98No%20Longer%20Actively%20Exploring%E2%80%99%20All3Media%20Acquisition%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689324997000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22http