content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F14123405%2F4.jpeg%20451w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F14123405%2F4-300x202.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663128%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22546%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20institutional%20and%20social%20systems%20that%20restrict%20the%20mobility%20and%20prospects%20of%20underprivileged%20people%20in%20Kapashera%20and%20Narela%20are%20complex%20and%20intertwined.%20Photo%3A%20Jignesh%20Mistry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApplying%20a%20Bourdieusian%20approach%20to%20understanding%20the%20urban%20class%20structure%20in%20Kapashera%20and%20Narela%20can%20makes%20it%20evident%20how%20economic%2C%20social%2C%20and%20cultural%20factors%20interact%20to%20produce%20various%20forms%20of%20exclusion%20and%20marginalisation%2C%20shaping%20social%20class.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20cultural%2C%20social%2C%20and%20economic%20resources%20available%20to%20individuals%20in%20these%20areas%20shape%20their%20social%20class%20and%20their%20opportunities%20for%20mobility.%20Lack%20of%20affordable%20public%20transport%20from%20these%20areas%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20city%2C%20for%20instance%20poses%20a%20huge%20barrier%20for%20upward%20social%20mobility.%20Even%20when%20equipped%20with%20niche%20skill%20sets%20and%20recruited%20by%20employers%20through%20non-governmental%20interventions%2C%20individuals%20in%20these%20areas%20rarely%20take%20up%20jobs%20in%20higher%20paying%20sectors%20due%20to%20the%20difficulty%20in%20commuting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fdelhi-bawana-challenges-students-women-education-school%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einterviews%20at%20Navjyoti%20Foundation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fdelhi-bawana-challenges-students-women-education-school%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENGO%20in%20Narela-Bawana%20area%20that%20provides%20skill%20training%20to%20youth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20coming%20from%20poorer%2C%20impoverished%20neighbourhoods%2C%20we%20found%20that%20most%20of%20them%20were%20hesitant%20in%20taking%20up%20jobs%20in%20Gurgaon%20or%20Noida%20where%20most%20of%20the%20companies%20were%20located.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commute%20was%20long%20and%20expensive%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiahousingreport.in%2Foutputs%2Fopinion%2Flandlord-tenant-dynamism-in-kapashera-urban-village-delhi%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eaffordable%20housing%20was%20an%20illusion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20these%20areas%20which%20are%20made%20for%20the%20upper%20class.%20Dominant%20cultural%20groups%20have%20more%20access%20to%20formal%20education%2C%20cultural%20institutions%2C%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20cultural%20capital%20that%20can%20help%20them%20achieve%20higher%20social%20status.%20This%20further%20perpetuates%20the%20vicious%20cycle%20of%20poverty%20and%20ensures%20the%20status%20quo%20of%20the%20class%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20institutional%20and%20social%20systems%20that%20restrict%20the%20mobility%20and%20prospects%20of%20underprivileged%20people%20in%20Kapashera%20and%20Narela%20are%20complex%20and%20intertwined.%20Addressing%20these%20issues%20requires%20an%20understanding%20of%20how%20economic%2C%20social%2C%20and%20cultural%20factors%20interact%20to%20shape%20social%20class.%20Policies%20and%20interventions%20based%20on%20Bourdieu%E2%80%99s%20perspective%20could%20focus%20on%20increasing%20access%20to%20formal%20education%20and%20cultural%20institutions%2C%20supporting%20the%20development%20of%20social%20networks%20and%20social%20capital%2C%20and%20addressing%20economic%20inequalities%20that%20limit%20opportunities%20for%20upward%20mobility.%20By%20adopting%20a%20Bourdieusian%20approach%2C%20policymakers%20can%20better%20understand%20how%20social%20class%20is%20shaped%20and%20how%20it%20can%20be%20addressed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3Cspan%3E%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20currently%20serving%20as%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20to%20the%20School%20of%20International%20Development%20and%20Global%20Studies%2C%20Faculty%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20University%20of%20Ottawa.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHima%20Trisha%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20Senior%20Research%20Analyst%20and%20Team%20(Co)Lead%20for%20Visual%20Storyboards%2C%20CNES.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShubhangi%20Derhgawen%3Cspan%3E%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20and%20a%20contributing%20research%20analyst%20for%20CNES.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%20Jignesh%20Mistry%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20Senior%20Research%20Analyst%20with%20CNES%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Visual%20Storyboards%20Team.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20study%20is%20produced%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EVisual%20Storyboards%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20team%20of%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20All%20photo%20credits%20belong%20to%20Jignesh%20Mistry.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20authors%20would%20like%20to%20especially%20thank%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMr.%20Suraj%20Kant%2C%20Ms.%20Swati%20Tiwari%2C%20Ms.%20Alka%20Singh%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efrom%20IYRC%20(Ideal%20Youth%20for%20Revolutionary%20Change)%2C%20Kapashera%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMr.%20Sushil%2C%20Ms.%20Neethu%20and%20Ms.%20Sheetal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efrom%20Navjyoti%20Fo